<bdy>

<b>Raymond's Algorithm</b> is a token based algorithm for <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../827/36827.xml">
mutual exclusion</link> on a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../501/8501.xml">
distributed system</link>.  It imposes a logical structure (a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../273/2145273.xml">
K-ary tree</link>) on distributed resources.  As defined, each node has only a single parent, to which all requests to attain the token are made.
<sec>
<st>
