</ss1>
<ss1>
<st>
Algorithm</st>

<p>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="number">

 If a node <it>i</it> wishes the receive the token in order to enter into its <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../312/638312.xml">
critical section</link>, it sends a request to its parent, node <it>j</it>.</entry>
<entry level="2" type="bullet">

 If node <it>j</it> FIFO is empty, node <it>j</it> shifts <it>i</it> into the its FIFO queue; <it>j</it> then issues a request to its parent, <it>k</it>, that it desires the token</entry>
<entry level="2" type="bullet">

 If node <it>j</it> FIFO queue is <it>not</it> empty, it simply shifts <it>i</it> into the queue</entry>
<entry level="1" type="number">

 When node <it>j</it> receives the token from <it>k</it>, it forwards the token to <it>i</it> and <it>i</it> is removed from the queue of <it>j''</it></entry>
<entry level="2" type="bullet">

 If the queue of <it>j</it> is not empty afterwarding the token to <it>i</it>, <it>j</it> must issue a request to <it>i</it> in order to get the token back</entry>
</list>
</p>
<p>

<it>Note</it>: If <it>j</it> wishes to request a token, and its queue is <it>not</it> empty, then it places itself into its own queue.  Node <it>j</it> will utilize the token to enter into its critical section <b>iff</b> it is at the head of the queue when the token is received.</p>

</ss1>
</sec>
<sec>
<st>
 Complexity </st>

<p>

Raymond's algorithm is guaranteed to be <it>O(log n)</it> per critical section entry if the processors are organized into a <it>K-ary</it> tree.  Additionally, each processor needs to store at most <it>O(log n)</it> bits because it must track <it>O(1)</it> neighbors.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>

